body:
### Problem

#35070 introduces the following bug:
```
vim.schedule callback: ...neovim/build/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/codelens.lua:263: Invalid buffer id: 9        
stack traceback:                                                                                                    
        [C]: in function 'nvim_buf_line_count'                                                                      
        ...neovim/build/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/codelens.lua:263: in function 'display_line_countdown'       
        ...neovim/build/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/codelens.lua:279: in function 'handler'                      
        ...s/neovim/build/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/client.lua:732: in function ''                             
        vim/_editor.lua: in function <vim/_editor.lua:0>
```

When deleting buffers (`:lua vim.api.nvim_buf_delete(0, { force = false })`) , that have been opened using `nvim *`. Checking if buffer is valid before calling `nvim_buf_line_count` seems to have fixed the problem on my build.

### Steps to reproduce

`minimal.lua `
```
-- Run this file as `nvim --clean -u minimal.lua`
for name, url in pairs({
  -- ADD PLUGINS _NECESSARY_ TO REPRODUCE THE ISSUE, e.g:
  -- 'https://github.com/author1/plugin1',
  -- 'https://github.com/author2/plugin2',
}) do
  local install_path = vim.fn.fnamemodify("nvim_issue/" .. name, ":p")
  if vim.fn.isdirectory(install_path) == 0 then
    vim.fn.system({ "git", "clone", "--depth=1", url, install_path })
  end
  vim.opt.runtimepath:append(install_path)
end

vim.api.nvim_create_autocmd("LspAttach", {
  desc = "LSP codelens",
  callback = function(args)
    local client = vim.lsp.get_client_by_id(args.data.client_id)
    if client and client:supports_method("textDocument/codeLens") then
      vim.api.nvim_create_autocmd({
        "BufEnter",
        "InsertLeave",
      }, {
        callback = function()
          vim.lsp.codelens.refresh({
            bufnr = 0,
          })
        end,
      })
    end
  end,
})

vim.lsp.config("luals", {
  cmd = { "lua-language-server" },
  filetypes = { "lua" },
  root_markers = {
    ".luarc.json",
    ".luarc.jsonc",
    ".luacheckrc",
    ".stylua.toml",
    "stylua.toml",
    "selene.toml",
    "selene.yml",
  },
  single_file_support = true,
  settings = {
    Lua = {
      runtime = {
        version = "LuaJIT",
      },
      hint = {
        enable = true,
        setType = true,
        paramType = true,
        paramName = "Disable",
        semicolon = "Disable",
        arrayIndex = "Disable",
      },
      completion = {
        callSnippet = "Replace",
      },
      doc = {
        privateName = { "^_" },
      },
      codeLens = {
        enable = true,
      },
      diagnostics = {
        globals = {
          "vim",
        },
      },
      workspace = {
        checkThirdParty = false,
        library = {
          vim.env.VIMRUNTIME,
          "${3rd}/luv/library",
          --  NOTE: lua testing framework
          -- "${3rd}/busted/library"
        },
      },
      telemetry = {
        enable = false,
      },
    },
  },
  log_level = vim.lsp.protocol.MessageType.Warning,
})

vim.lsp.enable("luals")
```


`nvim --clean -u minimal.lua *`
`:lua vim.api.nvim_buf_delete(0, { force = false })`

### Expected behavior

No error

### Nvim version (nvim -v)

NVIM v0.12.0-dev-afebbd0

### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?

not tested

### Operating system/version

Linux

### Terminal name/version

Gnome

### $TERM environment variable

xterm-256color

### Installation

repo
